11 SECTION 8. AMENDMENT. Section 37-15-16 of the North Dakota Century Code is
12 amended and reenacted as follows:
13 37-15-16. Administrator shall take charge of unclaimed estates of small value.
14 If a member of the veterans' home dies leaving property of the value of three thousand
15 dollars or less, the administrator immediately shall take charge of the property. If within forty-five
16 days of the date of death a valid claim of any heir or devisee is not made for the property and
17 an application or petition has not been filed for issuance of letters of administration, the
18 administrator shall convert the property into cash without probate or other proceedings and
19 make payment first toward reasonable funeral expenses and second toward reasonable and
20 necessary medical and hospital expenses of the last illness of the decedent. If any cash
21 remains, the administrator shall deposit the cash with the state treasurer who shall credit it to
22 the veterans' home operating fund. The administrator shall make a report of the administrator's
23 action to the administrative committee on veterans' affairs and the governor. The report must be
24 audited by, and included in the records of, the committee.
